orig=About the beginning of the month a small brig left here for Oporto, and was telegraphed as having arrived there on the 12th day after her departure from here - Even 21 days is considered a good passage generally. - at the end of the month a brig arrived here 90 days out from Sicily. - This will give some idea of the weather of late on the Atlantic mno|Local time: daily|QC flag: missing|Image File: StJohnsNFLDCas_USSI-401_M1958_1869-02-01_CP.jpg

orig=anytime this winter. I walked out [] the monthly mail steamer from Halifax, N. S. She put on full presence of steam and charged the ice, advancing about 2 1/2 ship lengths each time. The ice was quite firm right up to the ship's side, which I could touch with my hand - The steamer had received some damage from the severe weather. mno|Local time: daily|QC flag: missing|Image File: StJohnsNFLDCas_USSI-401_M1958_1869-02-01_CP.jpg
